						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In terms of concentration use, I have always been a buffing (vs debuffing) dirge. All five of my concentration points have been used by buffs. Anytime I have tried the opposite, replacing some or all with concentration using debuffs, I have noticed little/no/negative improvement.
<br />

<br />
However, with my play style (often long fights against near even or higher con mobs--often small groups) I have found the lvl 41 Bria's finally has an important spot in the mix. I am using it more often to keep from going oop.
<br />

<br />
That said, I now have a spare conc. point to throw around. I have been experimenting with mitigation debuff, slow, decrease str/agi. I think I have an answer, but I wondered if anyone else has any insights? Of course if you feel dropping Har's and doing all 3 debuffs is better, feel free to state your case.
<br />

<br />
(I mit debuff on single mobs, slow large groups, str/agi debuff late in the fight on groups of 2 or more).<br />_________________<br />Krescendo, 44 Kerran Dirge--Faydark
<br />
Bhandade, 43 Dorf Templar--Faydark</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
				</tr>
