							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Haste if it is trival, Boon if not.
<br />

<br />
Bria's because you have an extra spot.
<br />

<br />
JMoA, unless you are really sweeting the 7 more to a stat.
<br />

<br />
Proc song, because it isn't broken anymore.
<br />

<br />
Situationals-
<br />

<br />
Drop Bria's for Resists if a noxious mob that actually hurts.
<br />

<br />
If under 45, drop proc for Clara's.
<br />

<br />
Raid/Kite, drop least needed remaining buff for level 40 training option Selo's.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Now, level is everything... in your 20s, you just do what you can do.  In your 30s, this means more, you really can turn the fight and your choices affect the outcome of the group.  In part, this extended a little bit into the 40s.
<br />

<br />
In your late 40s, you could turn off all your buffs, put someone on autofollow, leave autoattack off, and go watch TV and no one would notice.
<br />

<br />
In fact, true story... several people would comment on how much your buffs help, and the tank would comment on your high caliber of play that night... since you did not grab aggro once.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Sonsi Carns
<br />
