							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Steppy, I guess I just need to experiment more. It is probably partially because  I am often the main dps guy in my groups (thats a pally/dirge/cleric only). I am just not noticing the difference. In addition, my party buffs never get resisted...on mobs a level or two higher and especially 50+ raid mobs (im 43 at the moment) sticking debuffs is sometimes difficult to darn near impossible.
<br />

<br />
Maybe I'm just lazy and looking for an excuse to leave the group buffs up and just run my specials routine. I am gonna play around some more.  I know the type groups I am in affect my perceptions. The tuff encounters for me seem more like hanging in there till the mob(s) is oop, then kicking the crap out of him.  
<br />

<br />
Debuffing mobs have taught me there is some value to going in full group buffs, then swapping to mob debuffs when they are lop/oop. Maybe switching on purpose might give me some insights.
<br />

<br />
Mog... being 43 I haven't really noticed a falloff yet, other than, perhaps the mobs health bard not dropping as much on my specials.
<br />

<br />
I wonder....could it be like EQI where we would hit the level wall, stat buffs would push past the "soft cap" making the increments we are adding nearly useless? I suppose a similar situation could exist for our debuffs as well...the mobs keep scaling but we are capped.
<br />

<br />
Maybe the coming expansion will help, maybe they'll balance a bit. I for one appreciate those who push the limits and find the flaws. I can't help but benefit the rest of us...hang in there.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Thanks guys.<br />_________________<br />Krescendo, 44 Kerran Dirge--Faydark
