						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Kind of.
<br />

<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;WARNING: HAPPY PLAYERS DO NOT READ HERE&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;
<br />

<br />
We rock, completely rock, the lower levels because once we get all our skills by the late 20s, we have all the tools we need to make our groups GOOD.  It does not take much to push an average level 30 into extrodinary.  A few stats, a few skills, and bit more damage per hit... boom, our group becomes the best night of everyone's careers.
<br />

<br />
We increase group DPS some much that we are the undisputed kings of DPS.
<br />
We increase tanking ability so much that it can be argued that we are equal to the tank we work our miracles through.
<br />
We make healing both more powerful, and less needed.  We even have a little ability in replacing the power needed to heal.
<br />

<br />
After having been a bard, I cannot fathom trying to survive in the 20s and 30s without a bard in the group.  I mean, is it even possible?  Our power is unquestioned.  Groups we decide to join should build shrines in our honor.
<br />

<br />
However, the game grows exponentially and our skills grow linearly.  Our trivial yet useful buffs like Bria's become drop in the ocean.  Our awesome abilities like Skills and Clara's become as trivial as the 2 points a tick Bria's was.
<br />

<br />
Players also get better gear, since they aren't going to outlevel it.  They have thier full spell lines.  They have gear which returns 4 times as much power as your Bria's.  They have traditions and items and other classes buffs which overpower your own skill buff.  Haste is virtually meaningless... with the amount of power regen they have, they never fall to autoattack only.  The only class that gets most of its damage from autoattack is, ironically, the bard.  Our proc song is half that of what is found on the most common of weapons.  Our stat buffs meant a lot more when they added up as much as the combined stats of the player's gear.  At 50, they add against 2 pieces of gear... and sometimes come up short.
<br />

<br />
Disconte never really meant all that much.  That is the diplomatic answer.  The real answer is that the spell has never once done a single thing as no one really believes MOBS even have attribute stats.  If they do, the formula does not make use of them.
<br />

<br />
Our slow fails to affect MOB CAs, which are the primary source of MOB damage.  This is to be considered unimportant, as there is a common hex doll that lets every player in the game cast a slow 1% less than our own.
<br />

<br />
Clara's for the longest time, was the ultimate saving grace of the Dirge.  It increased the group's DPS by about 20%.... HUGE.  Sadly, this spell is last upgraded at the end of the 30s, early 40s, I do not recall it has been so long.  I think it is 30s... it is blue on my bar, and I never have to locate the lower version when I mentor.  Sadly, it is tuned to those late 30s mobs.  The more powerful low 40s mobs aren't taking 20% more damage, but it is still acceptable.  Then, in the late 40s-50s... it just doesn't do much of anything at all.  Yes, if you parse it, it will still make the group do a LITTLE bit more damage.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Now, the obvious answer is, yes... we do in fact still stack with all these other things.  Having us in the group should still make the other 5 players even better than without us.  However, that is only surface deep.
<br />

<br />
Your buffs are trivial in impact.  The gear that makes them so uber now is accounted for in Mob Ability.  Your buffs and debuffs no longer move the scale past the bump... they barely move the scale at all.
<br />

<br />
So now you turn to your DPS as an equalizer.  While never something to write home about, your DPS was never laughable.  However, you will now find your personal DPS beaten not by just DPS classes... you are now in an unfamiliar realm, fighting the Priests and enchanters to stay out of last place.
<br />

<br />
Evac, the grand power of the scout, is now on every class and their brother.  Damn you cruel fates, as the ultimate power of the bard made evac almost unnessacary before... but now when we reach for you, we find it gone.  Disarming traps is hardly the danger it was before.  Safe Fall?  Pathfinding?  Nothing there.  JMoA got your guild JBoots... 10 levels ago.  They don't even wear the boots anymore...
<br />

<br />
Wait, we got something.... rez!  We got an awesome in combat rez, better than what preists get... we can rez those that fall while the priest never stop healing!!!  Except in most cases, once someone falls, its over.  Either you can rez and evac, or wipe.  Then an FD class pops up, rezzes the healer, and the raid pops back up.  Hardly an ability to build a case over at 44... would have been really welcome about 24.
<br />

<br />
SIX spots, total, in the group.  Add it up.  You no longer bring enough to the table.  Your personal DPS is lower than the broken summoner pet classes pets.  Your utility is about as high.
<br />

<br />
My guild still likes grouping with me.  Maybe they are remembering the old times.  Maybe they don't know that they are uber and I am not.  Maybe they are just being nice.  Maybe I am wrong.
<br />

<br />
What I do know is that they no longer have to hold off an event if the bard is not there.  They have a higher rate of success or an easier time on the same mobs when I am not present.  And when I look at the numbers, I feel like a total leech, like I have someone better's spot.
<br />

<br />
That feeling is making me have no fun.  They are supposedly adding my race to the game this week.  If they had locked an elf, riots would have broken out.  Lock the frog and barely a whimper.
<br />

<br />
The issue is there is absolutely no chance that i will be making a scout of any type.  My entire decisionmaking is between Warden and Warlock.
<br />

<br />
Is there anyone out there planning on making a dirge or troub on Befallen some time this week?  I would really hate to level to 40 without one.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Sonsi Carns
<br />
50  Human Dirge of Qeynos
<br />
Dawn of Evolution
<br />
Befallen
<br />

<br />
Beware the advice of successful people.
<br />
We do not seek company.</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
				</tr>
