							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Honest opinion here Sonsi.  If you really do hate being a Dirge that much now, just go ahead and make that Warden or Warlock.  You'll feel alot better.
<br />

<br />
Really though this sums it up for me.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">My guild still likes grouping with me. Maybe they are remembering the old times. Maybe they don't know that they are uber and I am not. Maybe they are just being nice. Maybe I am wrong.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
As long as you are getting groups and having fun does it really matter that we aren't quite fixed at the higest end atm?  Yes I've heard from you here and from other Dirges from other boards about how the higher end game breaks us.  But all of them say the same thing.  I still get groups all the time without any issue and they all ask if it's because people are just being nice.
<br />

<br />
Perhaps it's because we aren't as broke (yes we do have issues though I easily admit) as you feel we are?  Perhaps we are, I'm just saying there must be a reason why I have had to turn down invites for mid 40s areas already when I'm just sitting at level 39.  Or why when I log in my guild snaps me up.  I don't go LFG for long ever.  I think the most I have ever been flagged as such is around 30 minutes, and that was because I wasn't actively looking.
<br />

<br />
In the end I'm going to continue to look at these posts as just more of the same.  I've read posts about this and about that yet in game I've seen the exact opposite.  I've read about how Furies are broke as healers yet when I group with my guildmate I feel way more productive than before.  I've read how Brawler classes don't make decent tanks yet have had hours worth of fun doing high con groups with them.  The list goes on with things that I've read but haven't seen in game.  For now I'm just going to have to list this as yet another though.
<br />

<br />
I seriously hope though that either you can come to accept the fallbacks of the high end Dirge or at least move on to another class for now.  The game is about having fun and if you aren't, I hope you can find it.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><A HREF="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=191894106">Weep</A>
