							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Weep, I hear where you are coming from. Sometimes you see a rant and think, ok, here we go again. If its only one guy, and the same guy, you eventually learn to skip over them....if you are hearing from more than one place, take heed.
<br />

<br />
Consider this. Sony has a history of ignoring problems until there is a great uproar. Historically, Bard type characters, because, I think, they are played by some of the most skilled and cunning individuals (myself excluded) have alsways pushed the envelope and been the subject of "balancing" nerfs.In addition, low population classes often get ignored.  EQI had/has a long history of having weak classes at certain levels...when it goes on long enough those guys get a rep as perpetual LFG's.
<br />

<br />
If you sit back and be complacent, and your class is weak, eventually every finds out and you will be perpetually lfg.
<br />

<br />
Remember, you (and I) are comparing experiences way before these shortcoming evidently become apparent.  Maybe when we have worn those shoes for a while they'll rub a few blisters on us?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Last night my pc locked up in Permafrost, by the time I got back in I had the pleasure of watching my group go without me on a group with several giants. They were falling noticeably slower than when I was in group. It was very gratifying. It was late and I should have bowed out, but I was happy to be a useful part and rejoined....there was rejoicing. I really enjoy watching a mobs exp bar move when my special lands.
<br />

<br />
What would I have done if I had come back and gotten the comment, "wow, we never noticed you were gone!", or if I had made the same observation myself?
<br />

<br />
I for one don't wanna be a eunich (sic?) sucking exp off a group of guildmates/friends. I am really happy to have Mog rail against the system and maybe get it fixed before it affects me!
<br />

<br />

<br />
Oh, side note and back to the original thread....I was grouped with higher level troub last night. That gave me the opportunity to do much more debuffing than I usually do. Yes, I saw a lot of utility in my debuffs. However, I didn't get to compare me full buffing to full debuffing. We had two healers so mob attack debuffs were kind of pointless.....but, in so much as a person my age and disposition can keep an open mind, I am doing so, lol.<br />_________________<br />Krescendo, 44 Kerran Dirge--Faydark
