<br />

<br />
For me atm it seems either one of two things is happening.  Most people are happy with their Dirges at the high end, or the players who are level 50 just aren't actively voicing their concerns.  Having played MMORPGs for all this time now I just have a hard time believing that those players who are already level 50 and have been there for months wouldn't be making a bigger noise.  Perhaps for whatever reason the EQII community is different in that aspect, but I doubt it.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">If you sit back and be complacent, and your class is weak, eventually every finds out and you will be perpetually lfg.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
