<br />

<br />
I know I'm only 39 but again I've been invited to group with people in their mid 40s out of the blue.  "Sorry, I know you weren't LFG there but you wouldn't happen to want to join us in CT would you?"  Stuff like that just doesn't happen to friends who aren't a bard.  They go LFG and sit for an hour or two at times instead.  You yourself mention that you had a group notice that you were gone and were thrilled when you came back.  I've seen the same and I just don't see how it goes from being a valued member of a group to being a autofollow leech as continues to be the idea being continually espoused here.
<br />

<br />
