						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I understand and I agree with that.  I just don't agree with the way he has gone about trying to 'educate' everybody.  
<br />

<br />
Thott was capable of logging data and then expanding on that with well written thoughts on what exactly was broke and how best to go about fixinig it while still maintaining a decent balance compared to other classes.  Sonsi so far has attempted to do the same but it just comes off as somebody who hates the class he plays while souring those who are leveling up to it as well.  That's the thing that has bugged me most.  Not that he seems to generally care for the class and is trying to get it fixed, but that he is spreading a myth about how we are useless from 40 on.
<br />

<br />
I totally believe people when they say there are problems at the higher end and as I said I already have seen some of them with the way our (de)buffs don't scale well.  But there are better ways to get things fixed then to have 'SOE tells the Dirge, "SQUEAL LIKE A PIG!' as part of his sig on the official boards.  Or to answer a post questing Troub or Dirge with, "Reroll something that is NOT a scout before it is too late.".  Both of those things do nothing to advance the class or any forthcoming fixes to the class.
<br />

<br />
So yes while I do appreciate his zeal for the class and his apparent wanting to get things fixed, he honestly is doing more harm than good imo.  Constant spam on the official boards and here telling people to reroll, quit while they are ahead, etc.  He even goes so far as to argue with people from other classes who come to say that Dirges are far from worthless in their opinion.  He atm does nothing for the class except to further the idea by those who group with us that we are indeed worthless, and to make the numbers who do play our class lesser which makes it less likely to see timely fixes.  Yes he is a loud enough voice that the devs notice, but at the same time so does everybody else which is the problem in my eyes.
<br />

<br />
So if he wants to play the melodramatic savior role and claim he is done trying to save the class then oh well.
<br />

<br />
Ps, anybody that discounts what you have to say because of your level Steppy is a fool.  You were by far one of the best things about Diva when I still played EQ1.  As was Cujo also.<br />_________________<br /><A HREF="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=191894106">Weep</A>
<br />
Dirge of <A HREF="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/server.vm?serverId=106">Kithicor</A></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
