						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Fact is do i think dirges are useless no.....do i still like my class???? I indeed do i love my dirge! I just wish somethings were a little more consistent. My major gripe is the fact that we dont really stand out from troubs, we are seen as run speed.  And the sad but true fact is that at lvl 50 the run speed aint all that helpful anymore. I look forward to more scout balancing and i hope that the dirge is thrown some more bones in the future. 
<br />

<br />
I think that we are still a useable class, but that is only because there are not many of us at high levels, so we never really have to worry about stacking issues.  Now if there becomes more lvl 50's which indeed there are starting to be many more then the problems are going to start arising where we are not that useful. Raid situations, there imo is only really room for 1 dirge in the raid. Our mana regen is grp only and a coercer/illusionist is not so they can easily give crack to all raid members and theirs is much better. Claras is are only debuff worth using, and in raid situations it wouldnt stack with another dirge.
<br />

<br />
The main thing i think that bugs me however is the fact that we just dont stand out from a troub, and most of are good spells dont stack with them.  Trust me this is not a rant about troubs and i do not want to see troubs nerfed i think they are actually very well balanced atm.  I just dont see us being able to do anything that they cant. Our songsters luck line does not stack with a toub and they get the same spell, our mana regen does not stack with a troub and they get that spell too.  They also get the same debuff line(discante) as we do. We both get a haste line and they do stack unfortunatly they are pretty much useless unless at master 1 lvl.  We get our stat song buffs that does stack with them which is very nice, however with this song you will see no upgrade after lvl38 and the upgrade is not very useful because most of the time you will be using JMOA.  Our one saving grace and i thank soe for that is having by far the best REZ in the whole game. No healer can even touch our rez a 15 sec recast in combat rez that rezs at 44% health and power. The downside of this however is that it says specificaly in the description that it is not supposed to be in combat which I am very surprised has not been nerfed yet. I do see this coming in the near future though <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="Sad" border="0" /> . While we get this and claras....troubs get a mana drain, mana drain on almost all there attacks, the ability to stack stat buffing songs, many increase to defensive abilities on there songs,  can increase arcane and elemental dmg mitigation, and the ability to mez.
<br />

<br />
I really just want a dirge to stand out more, i think sonsi is very correct in saying at lvls 25 to early 40 range dirges are out standing at standing out however after that 40 mark none of there bread and butter spells upgrade and if they do it is a very minimal upgrade.  I think post lvl 40 some work will need to be done to help the dirge stand out from its alter-ego the troubador. This could be only me thinking this, however i repeat i do not think that the fix to this is changing anything on a troubador they are balnced imo. I think we need more spells like lanets, claras, and things of that nature to show what a dirge is really for.  Bottom line post 40 we increase grp dps% by a very small amount when compared to earlier lvls. 
<br />

<br />
Just my 2 copper<br />_________________<br />50 Dirge/ 21Provisioner of Befallen----Tarranth
<br />
31 Defiler/                                   ----Laups</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
